docs.abstract: Investigators outlined “a disturbing disregard” of privacy in a broad look at online tools used by political campaigns.
docs.snippet: Investigators outlined “a disturbing disregard” of privacy in a broad look at online tools used by political campaigns.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — The defunct political consulting firm Cambridge Analytica violated British law when it used improperly harvested Facebook data to aid Donald J. Trump’s 2016 presidential campaign, and would face a significant fine if it were not already in bankruptcy, Britain’s top data protection watchdog found Tuesday.

headline.main: Cambridge Analytica’s Use of Facebook Data Broke British Law, Watchdog Finds
headline.print_headline: Watchdog Finds Cambridge Analytica Misused Data

docs.abstract: Head-turning Allards, precursors to the hugely popular AC Cobra, are being built again by Roger Allard, who is not related to the original family.
docs.snippet: Head-turning Allards, precursors to the hugely popular AC Cobra, are being built again by Roger Allard, who is not related to the original family.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Allard J2 and J2X, rakish British sports cars stuffed with high-performance American V-8 engines, terrorized racetracks on both sides of the Atlantic from 1949 into the 1950s. Memories of the marque have faded with time, but it was a precursor to the hugely popular AC Cobra designed by Carroll Shelby.

headline.main: The Racecars Are Allards. He’s an Allard. There’s Just One Issue.
headline.print_headline: Allard Racecars, From That Other Allard

docs.abstract: The city’s tech elites were divided over the initiative, which is seen as an effort to hold their companies accountable for exacerbating the local housing crisis.
docs.snippet: The city’s tech elites were divided over the initiative, which is seen as an effort to hold their companies accountable for exacerbating the local housing crisis.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Voters in San Francisco approved a tax increase on the city’s largest businesses that would nearly double its budget for homeless services, a measure seen as an effort to hold wealthy technology companies accountable for exacerbating the local housing crisis.

headline.main: San Francisco Approves Business Tax to Fund Homeless Services
headline.print_headline: San Francisco Approves Tax To Fund Homeless Services

docs.abstract: Despite health insurance, terminally ill patients have to hunt around the world and on the internet for ways to stay alive.
docs.snippet: Despite health insurance, terminally ill patients have to hunt around the world and on the internet for ways to stay alive.
docs.lead_paragraph: JINZHOU, China — Zhang Zhejun used a fat plastic straw to gently tap the pale yellow pharmaceutical powder onto a piece of silver foil that lay on an electronic scale. He made sure the amount was just right before he poured it into a clear capsule.

headline.main: In China, Desperate Patients Smuggle Drugs. Or Make Their Own.
headline.print_headline: In China, the Desperate Make Medicine at Home
